-- DuPont says in technology transfer deal with UTEK
-- 
-- Tue Sep 25, 2007 3:08am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/25/us-dupont-utek-idUSN2533988420070925

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - U.S. chemical company DuPont Co ( DD.N ) on Tuesday unveiled a technology transfer alliance with UTEK Corp UTK.A. 

 UTEK, a technology transfer company, will make available DuPont's technologies to UTEK's customer base for a five-year period. Also, UTEK will search for appropriate technologies for possible transfer to DuPont's bio-based technology division. "These alliances will help DuPont broaden our technology reach so that we can deliver the greatest value from our extensive technology portfolio," Uma Chowdhry, DuPont's chief science and technology officer, said in a statement. (Reporting by  Lewis Krauskopf )